So excited I finally got to work with @daniel_alan_schnur on the installation and placement of my artwork in my new home! Dan has worked in countless museums and galleries and has a keen eye for design paired with the skill of properly hanging artwork. I observed him working in neighbors and friend’s apartments in my former buidling and always hoped I could work with him on my future space. Well today was that day! Dan came over and together we curated my pieces and styled art throughout my space. He hangs everything from not one center point but two side D rings so nothing will get crooked. Like when @pearl.in.newyork walks across the couch top and wacks her tail! This art isn’t budging. For now I’m sharing the living room but in time I’ll share all the corners he enhanced. Thank you Dan for helping to make my new apartment a home! I highly recommend reaching out to Dan for all your picture hanging needs. 

#danielschnur #artcurator #artinstallation #nycapartment #artisthome #brookehagel

social_posts.post_text:
It’s always a thrill to visit the new @metmuseum costume exhibit. For the 2023 spring/summer season that exhibit is Karl Lagerfeld: A Line of Beauty. The show was filled with fashion from his time at Chanel, Fendi and his own brand, with original sketches to go with each look. (Which you know I LOVE!) It was a beautiful curation, but I won’t be adding it to my list of best fashion exhibitions. I’ve come to expect a little more wow factor from a Met costume exhibit. 

#karllagerfeldalineofbeauty #costumeexhibition #themetropolitanmuseumofart #nycevent #chaneldesigner

Harry Winston’s annual hat luncheon was one for the books, and I had the privilege of custom illustrating a group of women in their stunning headwear. It was an honor to work with Harry Winston again, a brand that shares my passion for beauty and sophistication. The group illustration captured the essence of each woman and their individual style, and I am thrilled to have been able to capture such a memorable event for my client.

#fashionillustrationreels #fashionillustrator #brookehagel #harrywinston

In honor of #nationalinternday I wanted to take a look back at some of my internships which included Saturday Night Live as intern in Lorne Michaels office, Sex and the City as wardrobe intern to Patricia Fields and Cynthia Rowley as a design & pr intern. Interning was truly one of my favorite elements of college life. The experience you get is unparalleled to any classroom. It helps you mentally clear the path and pinpoint what you want to be doing in the future AND you graduate college with an amazing resume, giving you a leg up on the competition. It’s also much easier to land an internship than a job! Some of these companies and organizations don’t see much turnover and are highly sought after and competitive positions. Point being, if you can manage to carve out the time and have the opportunity for an internship (or three😉) take it! 

#internships #throwbackthursday #brookehagel #snl #cynthiarowley #sexandthecity
